OL,3,C'Bittersweet' moment for family as man
OL,4,Csentenced for killing former partner
OL,6,FThe court heard that Finlay had acted
OL,7,Fout of jealousy after Mrs Nelson had
OL,8,Fbegun a relationship with another man.
OL,9,FHer family embraced each other outside
OL,10,Fcourt after Finlay was sentenced to a
OL,11,Fminimum of 20 years.JIn a statement,
OL,12,Fthey described a "bittersweet" day,
OL,13,Fsaying that while they are relieved to
OL,14,Fsee the end of legal proceedings, the
OL,15,Fpain of their loss is immeasurable.
OL,16,F"Today is bittersweet. It may well be
OL,17,Fthe conclusion of legal proceedings,
OL,18,Fand for that we are relieved," they
OL,19,Fsaid.J"But for us as a family, the
OL,20,Fpain and sorrow caused by the loss of
OL,21,Four mum, sister, nanny and friend is
OL,22,Fimmeasurable ` and it will continue to
OL,23,Fbe so in the weeks, months and even
OL,24,Fthe years ahead.J"She will be sorely
OL,25,Fmissed by all who knew her."JAt the
OL,26,Ftariff hearing in Belfast Crown Court
